randoop.operation

Class GenericOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.operation.TypedOperation<CallableOperation>
      • randoop.operation.GenericOperation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Operation>, Operation

    public class GenericOperation
extends TypedOperation<CallableOperation>
    GenericOperation is an abstract implementation of Operation that represents an operation whose definition includes a type variable.

    An operation is represented as a GenericOperation if

    • it is defined in a GenericType in which case it may have concrete or generic type, or
    • it is a generic method or constructor of a concrete type.
    This variability means that at least one of the types associated with a GenericOperation must be generic, but the others may be concrete. So, all types are represented by GeneralType objects.

    Note that the declaring and output types of a creation operation are both defined as the type created.
